nflour mixture, watercress, water, yoghurt, stock paste (see tip), lemon juice and pepper then mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and cook <nobr>6 min\/100°C\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Taste and adjust seasoning as desired.","Pour sauce over quenelles, garnish with extra watercress and serve with rice."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Quenelles","content":["375 g white fish fillets, skinless, cut in pieces","1 tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground white pepper","½ tsp ground nutmeg","100 g unsalted butter, diced"]},{"title":"Panade","content":["30 g unsalted butter, diced","100 g milk","50 g plain flour","1 medium egg","1 egg yolk, from medium egg","2 egg whites, from medium eggs","600 g water"]},{"title":"Sauce","content":["1 Tbsp cornflour","100 g single cream","2 shallots, halved","30 g unsalted butter, diced","150 g watercress, plus extra for garnish","200 g water","100 g natural yoghurt","1 Tbsp chicken stock paste","½ lemon, juice only","ground black pepper, to taste"]}],"id":"r248386","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-9ImpxL31vY0\/XZQxVUc_vRI\/AAAAAAAAcuE\/tV9W6K9Ix28ymkUaVxb-C2H7YCQOu7BbACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_pjYsTtWxMu8tA8vV.png","title":"Quenelles with Watercress Sauce","publishedAt":"2017-11-20T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"27 g","fat":"46 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"20 g","calories":"2502 kJ \/ 598 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, serving plate, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> for the stock paste recipe."],"basicInfo":["advanced","40m","2h 45m","4 portions"]}